      • preContract

        void preContract()
        Performs pre-contract actions.

        This method is called from within an BeforeClass annotated method. It is therefore possible to throw a SkipException in this method.

      • getTypes

        AbstractTypes getTypes(Map<Class<?>,TypeElement> classTypeElementMap)
        Puts TypeElement instances into the given map (corresponding to the Class keys) and returns a AbstractTypes instance.

        Implementations of this method must put a TypeElement instance for each Class key into the given map. Implementations must not add or remove entries to/from the given map.

        Parameters:
        classTypeElementMap - Map with Class objects as keys. The value for each key is initially undefined and must be updated with the respective TypeElement upon return.
        Returns:
        the AbstractTypes instance that will be used for the contract test
